org.apache.freemarker.core.model.impl

Interface JavaMethodModel

  • All Superinterfaces:
    TemplateCallableModel, TemplateFunctionModel, TemplateModel, TemplateModelWithOriginName
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SimpleJavaMethodModel

    public interface JavaMethodModel
extends TemplateFunctionModel, TemplateModelWithOriginName
    Common super interface (marker interface) for TemplateFunctionModel-s that stand for Java methods; do not implement it yourself! It meant to be implemented inside FreeMarker only.

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        TemplateModel execute(TemplateModel[] args,
                      CallPlace callPlace)
               throws TemplateException
        Calls TemplateFunctionModel.execute(TemplateModel[], CallPlace, Environment), but it emphasizes that the Environment parameters is ignored, and passes null for it.
        Parameters:
        args - As getFunctionArgumentArrayLayout() always return null in JavaMethodModel-s, the length of this array corresponds to the number of actual arguments specified on the call site, and all parameters will be positional.
        callPlace - Same as with TemplateFunctionModel.execute(TemplateModel[], CallPlace, Environment).
        Throws:
        TemplateException

      • getFunctionArgumentArrayLayout
